            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>
        
<p>For all of the completionists out there, Mafia: The Old Country provides you with plenty to work towards to complete the entire game. </p>



<p>Hangar 13 returned to the franchise’s roots for <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/mafia-the-old-country-release-date-time/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mafia: The Old Country</a>. Instead of an <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/mafia-the-old-country-open-world/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">open world</a> as seen in Mafia 3, the latest installment is a linear-narrative driven game. As such, the game has a similar expected run time to the first two games of the series, meaning you can expect around <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/how-long-to-beat-mafia-the-old-country-game-length-explained/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">10-12 hours of content</a>. </p>



<p>Some fans assumed that less content is what led to the game receiving a $50 pricetag, but <a href="https://insider-gaming.com/mafia-the-old-country-devs-say-game-isnt-short-just-because-its-only-50/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Hangar 13</a> assured players that they won’t be “disappointed” by the final package. And although Mafia: The Old Country is shorter than other Triple AAA single-player offerings, there is still a long list of trophies and achievements to earn. </p>



<h2 id="h-how-to-get-every-mafia-the-old-country-achievement-amp-trophy">How to Get Every Mafia: The Old Country Achievement &amp; Trophy</h2>



<figure></figure>



